OL,3,CMP urges Prime Minister to define
OL,4,CIslamophobia to drive 'vitriol' off
OL,5,Cstreets
OL,7,FThe MP said: "Adopting this definition
OL,8,Fin Government, which successive
OL,9,FConservative prime ministers have
OL,10,Fneglected to do, will send a strong
OL,11,Fmessage that the racism and vitriol we
OL,12,Fare seeing by a minority of far-right
OL,13,Factivists on Britain's streets is
OL,14,Funacceptable and will not be
OL,15,Ftolerated."
OL,17,FThe previous Conservative government
OL,18,Fdeclined to adopt the proposed
OL,19,Fdefinition of Islamophobia and said
OL,20,Fthe wording could harm freedom of
OL,21,Fspeech.
OL,26,@oD@NOUwD@KO]
